ce:section.ce:para:
Once the COMSOL model was validated with successful cleaning results achieved in previous experiments, this numerical methodology is applied to a 6 in. schedule 40 API 5L/A106 carbon steel seamless tube with 168 mm outer diameter, 7.11 mm wall thickness and 6 m length. The present paper conducts a parametric study to investigate the optimal HPUT array (see Fig. 3
                        ) with water filled within the pipe (static), fouling, signal input and fluid temperature. The model focuses on a 40 kHz Langevin bolt-clamped HPUT due to its successful cleaning in prior experiments [8,14,46]. The pipe is monitored at different locations along its length to compare the various parameters as shown in Fig. 4
                        . The points are placed at 1 m distances on the inner and outer walls of the pipe to monitor the acoustic pressure within the liquid and the solid displacement on the outer wall of the pipe.
